OL,6,FIf the government were to end the non-
OL,7,Fdom tax break, and simultaneously cut
OL,8,Femployee national insurance, Labour
OL,9,Fitself would have even less money than
OL,10,Fit fears for its spending priorities -
OL,11,Funless it were to reverse Tory tax
OL,12,Fcuts, which it has said it does not
OL,13,Fwish to do.
OL,15,FWhat the Chancellor ultimately decides
OL,16,Fwill be conditioned by the OBR's last
OL,17,Ftwo forecasts of the and spending,
OL,18,Fwhich he will receive in coming days.
